This project defines a class for simplifying queries and updates over a database connection.
It allows you submit SELECTs, INSERTs, UPDATEs and DELETEs to a JDBC-connected  database
without having to know SQL.

The entry point for using this project is the following class:

	DbConnection			encapsulates request-handling for a database connection.

	
See the TestDbConnectionPositiveTests.java JUnit test case for an example of performing
queries, inserts and deletes.

See the GeMHa project for example use of these classes, especially AcceptMessagesFromQueue.java and
StoreMesssageToQueue.java.